    <description>The Mariner 7 Spacecraft Ultraviolet Spectrometer (UVS) was an instrument on NASA's Mariner 7 spacecraft, which flew by Mars in 1969. It was designed to study the composition of the Martian atmosphere and surface by measuring ultraviolet light. The UVS helped identify atmospheric components like carbon dioxide and detected the presence of thin layers of ozone. The data collected contributed to a better understanding of Mars' atmosphere and its potential for sustaining life.  </description>
